  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, how was your break from work — did it feel like that 20-minute walk you described, a little reset?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, not really... I just stared at the ceiling, thinking about work. You know, that feeling when your brain won't \"shut up\"? Frustrating."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, that brain-on-loop feeling is rough. It can take over even when you're trying to rest. What helps you break out of it?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Sometimes I try to watch a Bollywood movie, but even that doesn't help. My mind keeps going back to work deadlines and meetings. It's so annoying."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That makes sense — Bollywood is usually a good escape. Maybe this time, the stress just stayed with you. What kind of movie do you usually watch when you need to unwind?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Normally I go for old Shah Rukh Khan films. You know, the masala ones with songs and action. But even those aren't working today. Not sure why. My head is just stuck."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Old Shah Rukh Khan films are a great pick for unwinding — fun, songs, and drama. It’s weird when even that doesn’t work. What’s one small thing that feels like a reset for you these days?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly... I don’t know. Usually, playing cricket helps, even just a few throws in the garden. But today, even that feels like too much. Maybe I need to try something new. Or maybe just let my mind be frustrated for a while. *shrugs*"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "It’s okay to feel stuck sometimes — no need to fix it right away. If you did pick something new, what would it be? Something tiny, just to shift the rhythm?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe something like cooking? I haven’t cooked in a while, but it feels like a small task that doesn’t require much thinking. Or maybe just a short walk without the phone, just to clear my head. Not sure yet."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Cooking or a phone-free walk — both are great tiny resets. They give your mind something gentle to focus on. What’s easier for you to try first?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe the walk? It’s easier to just step out for 10 minutes, no plans. Cooking feels like there’s pressure to *do* something right. But I’ll think about it. Thanks."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "A short walk is perfect — no plans, just movement and fresh air. Let me know how it lands. And take your time thinking about the rest."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I’ll try the walk. Maybe the fresh air will help, *baarish ki tarah* just wash away the stress for a bit. Thanks for the idea."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome — and I love the *baarish ki tarah* comparison. A little rain or a walk, both can help the mind reset. Let me know how it goes!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’ll try it, maybe after lunch. If it doesn’t help, I’ll give cooking a shot. Thanks again — and yeah, *baarish* can really help. *Sach mein*."
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're very welcome — and *sach mein*, a little rain or a walk can work wonders. Just take it one small step at a time. I'm here if you want to talk about it later."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I’ll give it a shot. Maybe the weather will help — if it rains, I can pretend I’m washing away the stress *ki tarah* I said. Haha. Thanks again, Maya."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome, Priyansh — and I love the idea of pretending the rain is washing it all away. Sometimes a little imagination helps the most. Let me know how it goes!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Alright, I should head out now. Gotta get back to work, but this chat helped a bit. Thanks again, Maya. *Bas itna hi.*"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome — and I'm glad the chat helped even a little. Go take that walk, and if the rain comes, enjoy the mood it brings. *Bas itna hi*, for now!"
    }
  ],
